  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "TensorFlow is an open source platform for machine learning. Prior to versions 2.9.0, 2.8.1, 2.7.2, and 2.6.4, the implementation of `tf.raw_ops.DeleteSessionTensor` does not fully validate the input arguments. This results in a `CHECK`-failure which can be used to trigger a denial of service attack. Versions 2.9.0, 2.8.1, 2.7.2, and 2.6.4 contain a patch for this issue.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2022-29194 describes a vulnerability in TensorFlow's DeleteSessionTensor input validation causing a denial of service. TensorFlow is a core ML/AI framework; this is a software supply-chain vulnerability affecting AI pipelines that depend on the library. Evidence: CVE description, affected versions, patches, references."
  },
